<taxonomicName id="4192A413270444C383A085DD6040E98A" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ishiharai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ishiharai">
<emphasis id="13EC3785B94EEB2CF5B618EB15226326" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ishiharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), absence of dark spots between the longitudinal ridges on the elytra (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="51883AEA1CE79D8B0B6B92031601A553" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Habitus of Pyrrhalta ishiharai Kimoto and P. wulaiensis sp. nov. A P. ishiharai, female, typical form, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. wulaiensis sp. nov., female, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545564" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">34D</figureCitation>
) (dark spots present between longitudinal ridges on elytra in 
<taxonomicName id="3A2AE4AC68851F78F870E4C9058976F1" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ishiharai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ishiharai">
<emphasis id="68AB5B7B0C39B6C3C905AA6100546626" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ishiharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fig. 
<figureCitation id="01D3EE660A21B6C93A579FDF3E37F2A5" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Habitus of Pyrrhalta ishiharai Kimoto and P. wulaiensis sp. nov. A P. ishiharai, female, typical form, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. wulaiensis sp. nov., female, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545564" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">34A</figureCitation>
), lacking apical spine on tibia and normal tarsomere I of middle leg in males (apical spine present on tibia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92CB5FDD18685BBCFADB8BD30299B178" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta ishiharai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of tibia of middle leg, male F abdominal ventrite VIII G spermatheca H tarsi of middle leg, male I abdominal ventrite V, female J abdominal ventrite V, male K gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545565" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">35E</figureCitation>
) and modified tarsomere I of middle leg in males of 
<taxonomicName id="5C5C76BB725A51D2D727584D32B91785" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ishiharai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ishiharai">
<emphasis id="FB402FF85A1B7CB0709F5AA0C6FBC74F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ishiharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="909FF1C683B075DDE24800D7AD4D5B42" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta ishiharai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of tibia of middle leg, male F abdominal ventrite VIII G spermatheca H tarsi of middle leg, male I abdominal ventrite V, female J abdominal ventrite V, male K gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545565" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">35H</figureCitation>
)), transverse ostium and medially curved aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1C8E851F3D6032662915E015144A6D24" captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta wulaiensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545566" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36C, D</figureCitation>
) (in longitudinal ostium and recurved at apical 1/3 of aedeagus 
<taxonomicName id="E3A81B6A88DC1999111E2A80629984F7" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ishiharai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ishiharai">
<emphasis id="97C6EA9C33455A99E04D6C5FA0583D45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ishiharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FD662985DD8DF4E14B0C30AC84614144" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta ishiharai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of tibia of middle leg, male F abdominal ventrite VIII G spermatheca H tarsi of middle leg, male I abdominal ventrite V, female J abdominal ventrite V, male K gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545565" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">35C, D</figureCitation>
