<subSubSection id="BBF4C3483094804139DBF48FE94779F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="534B58220C5BCC16D7972AA0789E87FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="534C5B08A1AC1E058C5B0644C3BC1981" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The species is widespread at lowlands (0-1,500 m) in northern Taiwan and mid-altitudes (1,500-2,500 m) in central Taiwan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0F6F2E25142C922EB335FC2388C32C1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CE0D751DC78A4F84F4A5D063862BC036" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B2FD220227A54C4C91F15B8620E1CD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The species is named for the locality where specimens were collected and used for laboratory rearing.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
